fields.qnDesc: The Hackers changed our admin password and now we can't access the system. But they have embedded the password in the Source for easy access. Find it, Use it.
Password for user files were stored as a txt file and now that file has been deleted. Enter the password to access the files.
Web Robots are programs that traverse the Web automatically. In the current situation these might be able to help us.
Okay, Now we know that 'Send Password' button sends the password to someone. Can you Redirect it?
This looks easy right? The password is already given. But wait, the attacker must have altered it. We also know that the password length is 32 characters. Is there any hash function with that length?
